<subSubSection id="C321652DFFC1C21DF3C23CD8FCBF9D4B" pageId="5" pageNumber="59" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8B8436A6FFC1C21DF3C23CD8FCBF9D4B" blockId="5.[151,1436,1226,1423]" pageId="5" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis id="B94FEAB4FFC1C21DF3C23CD8FEAB9D06" bold="true" box="[199,345,1260,1284]" pageId="5" pageNumber="59">Distribution.</emphasis>
New for 
<collectingCountry id="F32C7636FFC1C21DF2B93CD9FDF79D06" box="[444,517,1261,1284]" name="Ghana" pageId="5" pageNumber="59">Ghana</collectingCountry>
. Described and until now only known from the 
<typeStatus id="54808804FFC1C21DF0FB3CD9FBDE9D06" box="[1022,1068,1261,1284]" pageId="5" pageNumber="59">type</typeStatus>
series collected in NE 
<collectingCountry id="F32C7636FFC1C21DF6253CD9FE7A9D25" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="5" pageNumber="59">Democratic Republic of the Congo</collectingCountry>
(“Uele, Paulis”). The new data from 
<collectingCountry id="F32C7636FFC1C21DF0103D24FCA89D25" box="[789,858,1296,1319]" name="Ghana" pageId="5" pageNumber="59">Ghana</collectingCountry>
suggest that the species has a much wider distribution and is probably connected through a zone of tropical rain forests.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C321652DFFC1C21DF3C23D60FF169E5D" pageId="5" pageNumber="59" type="discussion">
